            </div>
            <div class="cell small-12 medium-6 large-6 flex-container">
                <div class="callout light-grey flex-child-auto">
                    <p class="text-center h5 sans-serif bold">When do I call UT Police (210) 567-8911?</p>
                    <p>
                        Call the UT Health Science Center Police Department when there is imminent danger, such as an
                        emergency situation, concern about dangerous or unusual behavior or a feeling that something is
                        just not right.
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>911 – Call this number from any campus phone for immediate assistance</li>
                        <li>(210) 567-8911 – Program this emergency number into your mobile device to call campus
                            police.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="cell small-12 medium-6 large-6 flex-container">
                <div class="callout light-grey flex-child-auto">
                    <p class="text-center h5 sans-serif bold">When do I call (210) 567-CARE (2273)?</p>
                    <p>
                        Call 567-CARE to share a concern about a Health Science Center colleague, friend or perhaps even
                        yourself, who may need help in dealing with a difficult situation.
                    </p>
                    <p>
                        This is a nonemergency phone number answered by the UT Health Science Center Police Department.
                        Dispatchers will help determine whether an immediate response is needed or whether a referral
                        for assistance is the best approach.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
